{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"indecisive-callous-armyworm","description":"# Cupid enrichment op: LLM ticket-digest extractor + digest schema\n\n## Why\nSemantic overlap detection needs a compact, normalized per-ticket representation that catches paraphrase (\"login broken\" vs \"users can't authenticate\") WITHOUT embeddings or a vector DB — keeping rebar on its Anthropic-only, no-heavy-ML grain. The Cupid pattern (arXiv:2308.10022) uses the LLM as a one-time feature extractor: expensive semantics amortized per-ticket, cheap lexical match forever after.\n\n## What\nA new LLM operation that reads a ticket's full text and emits a structured dedup digest, plus the JSON output-schema for it. Modeled on the existing op scaffolding in `src/rebar/llm/operations.py` / `src/rebar/llm/completion.py` (RunRequest, mode=\"structured\", output_schema; prompt in the library with front-matter).\n\nDigest shape: `{problem_keywords[], component_or_area, key_entities[], propositions[]}` — 2-6 atomic problem/repro propositions; logs, stack traces, and code explicitly discarded. Deterministic/idempotent given the same input (no timestamps in the payload) so re-extraction of unchanged content reproduces the digest.\n\n## Scope\n- New op module (e.g. `src/rebar/llm/enrich.py`) + library entry in `src/rebar/__init__.py`.\n- Prompt in the prompt library (`src/rebar/llm/reviewers/` or `.rebar/prompts/`) with front-matter `execution_mode: 1-TURN`.\n- Output schema registered under `src/rebar/schemas/` and validated via `structured.py`.\n- IN scope: the extraction op + schema + prompt + eval fixtures for extraction quality.\n- OUT of scope: storage (S2), the queue (S3), the drain (S4), retrieval (S5/S6).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `rebar.llm.enrich(ticket_id)` (and an internal callable) returns a validated digest `{problem_keywords, component_or_area, key_entities, propositions}` for a ticket.\n- [ ] Logs/stack-traces/code are excluded from the digest; only dedup-relevant essence is kept.\n- [ ] The op is idempotent: identical input text yields an identical digest payload (no timestamps/nondeterministic fields).\n- [ ] Disabled/absent-LLM path raises/reports cleanly so callers can gracefully skip (no partial writes).\n- [ ] Eval fixtures assert extraction captures the core problem/entities on representative tickets (including epic-sized bodies up to ~4000 tokens).","id":"ee3d-fc7b-e280-4cbb","parent_id":"bd83-c56f-1f72-4ef2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Cupid enrichment op: LLM ticket-digest extractor + digest schema"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783568197150319001,"uuid":"6c967af0-f53f-49b1-ace7-5e03e7dd3491"}